amâEngland war (1687) and the invasion of Burmese Lanna in 1662.\n\nNevertheless, the presence of numerous foreigners from the French Jesuits to the\nPersian delegates has left historians with rich sources of material on the city\nof Ayutthaya and its courtly life in the seventeenth century that otherwise\nwould not have survived the complete destruction of the capital in 1767.\n","linknr":317,"url":"Narai","recorded":1375074951,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Narai&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Narai&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Lavo_Kingdom","/wiki/Shiojiri,_Nagano","/wiki/File:Narai.JPG","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f2/Narai.JPG/220px-Narai.JPG","/wiki/List_of_Thai_Monarchs","/wiki/Si_Suthammaracha","/wiki/Phetracha","/wiki/Yothathep","/wiki/Royal_house","/wiki/Prasat_Thong","#cite_note-siri-1","#cite_note-nama-2","/wiki/Thai_language","/wiki/Thai_language","/wiki/Ayutthaya_Kingdom","/wiki/Constantine_Phaulkon","/wiki/Louis_XIV","/wiki/Mandarin_(bureaucrat)#History_and_use_of_the_term","/wiki/Siamese_revolution_of_1688","/wiki/Siam%E2%80%93England_war_(1687)","/wiki/Lanna","#Succession","#Domestic_Policy","#Foreign_Missions","#Rising_French_influence","#The_.